00:34.400 --> 00:38.360
The Land Before Time XIV

00:38.680 --> 00:42.800
Journey of the Brave (2016)

00:42.920 --> 00:46.920
NARRATOR: <i>Long, long ago,</i>
<i>in the Land Before Time,</i>

00:47.880 --> 00:50.520
<i>great beasts ruled the world.</i>

00:52.640 --> 00:55.240
<i>These mighty beasts</i>
<i>were the dinosaurs.</i>

00:58.720 --> 01:02.200
<i>Yes, it was a place of wonder,</i>

01:03.680 --> 01:05.519
<i>but also filled with danger...</i>

01:05.600 --> 01:07.480
(ROARS)

01:07.680 --> 01:09.480
<i>...where survival was uncertain</i>

01:10.360 --> 01:13.040
<i>and families were sometimes</i>
<i>torn apart.</i>

01:19.280 --> 01:20.240
(CROAKS)

01:22.080 --> 01:25.720
<i>Which is how the young</i>
<i>Longneck named Littlefoot</i>

01:26.720 --> 01:30.720
<i>came to live with his grandmother,</i>
<i>grandfather,</i>

01:31.360 --> 01:33.680
<i>and his close friends</i>

01:33.760 --> 01:36.720
<i>in the beautiful Great Valley.</i>

01:43.960 --> 01:49.560
<i>The perils of the world had</i>
<i>claimed his mother and</i>
<i>separated him from his father.</i>

01:51.680 --> 01:55.040
<i>Then, a miraculous day came.</i>

01:55.560 --> 01:59.360
<i>Littlefoot and his father,</i>
<i>Bron, were reunited.</i>

02:01.640 --> 02:03.840
<i>During the time they were apart,</i>

02:03.920 --> 02:08.039
<i>Bron had become</i>
<i>the leader of a large migrating herd.</i>

02:08.759 --> 02:12.240
<i>This meant he couldn't stay</i>
<i>with Littlefoot in the Great Valley.</i>

02:14.600 --> 02:16.480
<i>Bron wanted his son to join him,</i>

02:17.400 --> 02:19.640
<i>and Littlefoot wanted</i>
<i>to be with his father,</i>

02:20.040 --> 02:22.320
<i>but he also didn't want</i>
<i>to leave his home.</i>

02:26.680 --> 02:30.840
<i>So Littlefoot made the tough decision</i>
<i>to stay with his grandfather,</i>

02:30.920 --> 02:33.080
<i>grandmother and friends.</i>

02:37.560 --> 02:39.480
<i>Now each year,</i>

02:39.560 --> 02:42.960
<i>when the Season of New Growth</i>
<i>follows the Cold Time,</i>

02:43.040 --> 02:46.240
<i>and the warm sunshine</i>
<i>falls softly on the Great Valley,</i>

02:48.120 --> 02:51.120
<i>Littlefoot looks forward</i>
<i>to a visit from his father,</i>

02:51.400 --> 02:55.240
<i>leading the great herd</i>
<i>on their yearly migration.</i>

02:58.760 --> 03:02.360
<i>It's a reunion he dreams</i>
<i>about all year long.</i>

03:09.680 --> 03:12.160
<i>And it will be happening today.</i>

03:14.280 --> 03:15.240
(GASPS)

03:16.440 --> 03:18.120
Today's the day!

03:23.040 --> 03:24.560
(GROWLS)

03:26.040 --> 03:28.240
(ROARING)

03:32.480 --> 03:33.920
(RUBY GIGGLING)

03:35.000 --> 03:37.080
(GIGGLING)
You can't find me!

03:39.840 --> 03:41.760
(ROARING)

03:43.240 --> 03:44.480
(GIGGLES)

03:45.760 --> 03:48.600
Come on, Littlefoot,
we're playing hide
from the Sharptooth!

03:48.680 --> 03:49.760
Come and play!

03:50.400 --> 03:53.200
Can't, Ruby!
My dad's coming today!

03:56.320 --> 03:58.160
Mr. Threehorn,
is Cera around?

03:58.240 --> 04:00.080
She's gone
to the swimming hole.

04:01.440 --> 04:02.640
What's the hurry?

04:02.720 --> 04:04.920
Today's the day
my dad comes back!

04:16.279 --> 04:19.399
(SINGING) <i>Hey, hey, hey</i>
<i>Today's the day</i>

04:19.519 --> 04:23.000
<i>My dad's coming home</i>
<i>from far away</i>

04:23.040 --> 04:26.880
<i>We'll race and we'll run</i>
<i>and we'll laugh and play</i>

04:26.960 --> 04:29.600
<i>I feel so happy that I gotta say</i>

04:30.720 --> 04:34.040
<i>Hey, hey, hey</i>
<i>Today is the day</i>

04:40.680 --> 04:44.080
<i>Yep, yep, yep</i>
<i>The time is near</i>

04:44.160 --> 04:47.240
<i>Our brothers and sisters</i>
<i>will soon be here</i>

04:47.320 --> 04:51.000
<i>I will teach them to swim</i>
<i>and to be your friend</i>

04:51.400 --> 04:52.360
(GASPS)

04:52.440 --> 04:55.200
You will teach them
to stay away from your rear end.

04:55.320 --> 04:56.400
Yeah.

04:56.480 --> 04:59.520
<i>Hey, hey, hey</i>
<i>Today is the day</i>

04:59.600 --> 05:01.200
PETRIE: Hey, guys!

05:02.080 --> 05:04.080
<i>It spring! It spring</i>

05:04.160 --> 05:07.800
<i>And me feel like flying</i>

05:09.880 --> 05:13.280
<i>In spring no one be</i>
<i>grumpy or grouch</i>

05:15.480 --> 05:16.600
(CROAKS)

05:16.800 --> 05:21.160
<i>When me up in the air and skying</i>

05:22.200 --> 05:25.040
Oh! Hey! Oh! Wait! Ohh!

05:25.880 --> 05:27.280
Whoa!

05:27.440 --> 05:28.680
(SPLASHES)

05:30.400 --> 05:31.560
Ouch.

05:32.160 --> 05:35.120
You just barely missed
the hatchlings, Petrie!

05:35.200 --> 05:37.720
Oh, Petrie real sorry.

05:38.000 --> 05:40.600
They're not born yet,
they can't hear you.

05:41.960 --> 05:43.640
No listen to her.

05:45.840 --> 05:46.920
Ahh!

05:49.880 --> 05:51.160
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

05:51.240 --> 05:53.880
Hey, guys,
you know what day
today is?

05:54.080 --> 05:55.200
I do!

05:57.040 --> 05:59.800
<i>Hey, hey, hey</i>
<i>Today's the day</i>

06:00.040 --> 06:03.360
<i>When I'm gonna</i>
<i>blow that rock away</i>

06:03.520 --> 06:07.000
<i>I'll hit it so hard</i>
<i>it'll break in two</i>

06:07.520 --> 06:10.600
<i>You'll be amazed</i>
<i>at what I can do</i>

06:11.240 --> 06:12.920
<i>Hey, hey, hey</i>

06:13.280 --> 06:14.960
Okay. Get ready!

06:16.360 --> 06:17.720
(GRUNTS)
(THUDS)

06:22.320 --> 06:23.480
What did I tell you?

06:23.800 --> 06:25.440
<i>I moved the rock</i>

06:25.680 --> 06:27.200
<i>We are very, very glad</i>

06:27.400 --> 06:28.880
<i>Me fly so high</i>

06:28.960 --> 06:30.680
<i>I'm gonna see my dad</i>

06:30.880 --> 06:32.160
<i>It the flying-est</i>

06:32.320 --> 06:33.720
<i>Swimming-est</i>
<i>Happiest</i>

06:33.880 --> 06:34.800
<i>Spring-iest</i>

06:34.880 --> 06:36.120
ALL: <i>Day</i>

06:36.240 --> 06:38.960
<i>Today's the day!</i>

06:39.040 --> 06:42.480
DUCKY: <i>Today is the day!</i>
CERA: <i>Hey, hey</i>

06:42.680 --> 06:43.960
LITTLEFOOT:
<i>Today's the day</i>

06:44.080 --> 06:46.400
ALL: <i>Today's the day!</i>

06:46.480 --> 06:48.280
(SPIKE SIGHS)

06:49.600 --> 06:51.120
(ALL LAUGH)

06:51.280 --> 06:52.600
(CRACKING)
(GASPING)

06:52.680 --> 06:54.120
The eggs.

06:54.360 --> 06:55.600
(CRACKING)

06:59.600 --> 07:01.000
Ohh!

07:01.840 --> 07:03.480
(CHIRPING)

07:03.760 --> 07:05.880
(CHUCKLES)
Hello, little guy.

07:07.360 --> 07:08.320
Hey.

07:08.480 --> 07:10.760
(LAUGHING)
He got you, Petrie!

07:11.040 --> 07:12.440
He sure do.

07:12.520 --> 07:13.760
(ALL LAUGH)

07:15.880 --> 07:17.360
(CHIRPING)

07:19.760 --> 07:21.200
So cute.

07:21.280 --> 07:23.480
I am Ducky,
your sister.

07:23.880 --> 07:25.200
(CHIRPING)

07:25.880 --> 07:28.360
And this is Spike,
your adopteded brother.

07:28.600 --> 07:29.800
(MOANS PLEASANTLY)

07:33.160 --> 07:36.440
And me Petrie,
your adopteded brother's...

07:36.480 --> 07:38.280
Uh...

07:38.360 --> 07:40.280
Me just Petrie.
(LAUGHS)

07:40.400 --> 07:41.360
(LAUGHS)

07:54.440 --> 07:55.680
(CHIRPING)

07:57.920 --> 08:00.240
(LOUD FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

08:05.280 --> 08:07.120
Grandpa! Grandma!

08:09.080 --> 08:10.520
Look, it's the hatchlings!

08:11.960 --> 08:13.360
(MOANS)

08:14.440 --> 08:17.600
Ah. What a special today
this is.

08:18.400 --> 08:22.520
Today! I forgot.
Today's the day my dad comes back!

08:23.000 --> 08:24.360
Great!
Special day!

08:24.720 --> 08:27.240
We are so happy for you,
yes, we are.

08:28.160 --> 08:29.960
Can we go watch
for him?

08:30.080 --> 08:33.039
(LAUGHS) I thought
you might want to.

08:35.120 --> 08:36.679
Come, Littlefoot.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.360
Now, Grandpa,
keep an eye on the ice.

08:43.799 --> 08:45.040
It's still slippery.

08:45.440 --> 08:46.720
We will, Grandma.

08:47.240 --> 08:48.480
Come on.

09:01.320 --> 09:04.800
We're lucky to live
in such bounty, Littlefoot.

09:04.960 --> 09:06.840
Not many of our kind do.

09:09.440 --> 09:12.480
There they are!
My dad's herd!

09:13.240 --> 09:14.600
You're right, Littlefoot.

09:16.880 --> 09:19.960
But where's my dad?
I don't see him.

09:20.920 --> 09:24.680
That is strange.
Bron is always
at the head of the herd.

09:25.520 --> 09:27.960
I'm sure there's nothing
to worry about.

09:28.400 --> 09:29.560
WILD ARMS: Help!

09:29.640 --> 09:31.520
Help!

09:32.640 --> 09:34.360
Help!

09:34.520 --> 09:35.640
Who's that?

09:35.680 --> 09:37.200
We'd better
take a look.

09:42.560 --> 09:43.960
(SCREAMING)

09:46.040 --> 09:47.800
Help!
Oh, I'm safe.

09:48.120 --> 09:49.440
Am I really here?

09:49.520 --> 09:51.000
Somebody pinch me,
please.

09:53.120 --> 09:55.720
No! Not you!
No. Not you. (LAUGHS)

09:55.800 --> 09:57.200
I'll pinch myself.

09:57.680 --> 10:00.160
Ow! Ouch.

10:00.280 --> 10:01.480
Why did I do that?

10:01.600 --> 10:03.240
And you are?

10:03.840 --> 10:06.800
I, uh... Well, everybody
calls me Wild Arms,

10:06.880 --> 10:08.960
though I never really figured out why.

10:11.160 --> 10:14.560
Oh. (LAUGHS)
That makes so much sense now!

10:15.720 --> 10:17.080
What happened, Wild Arms?

10:17.400 --> 10:19.280
Aw, I mean what didn't happen?

10:19.360 --> 10:21.480
The earth shook
and spit liquid fire.

10:21.560 --> 10:24.200
And the heat...
Like you've never seen before!

10:25.320 --> 10:27.360
But, it's too upsetting
to talk about.

10:28.000 --> 10:31.560
But if you must know,
it all started with a horrible boom!

10:33.160 --> 10:34.840
<i>The Fire Mountain exploded.</i>

10:34.880 --> 10:38.480
<i>It just blew its top.</i>
<i>Fire everywhere you looked.</i>

10:39.760 --> 10:41.040
<i>There was no escape.</i>

10:43.880 --> 10:46.680
<i>And the Longnecks, oh,</i>
<i>they were hit the hardest.</i>

10:48.000 --> 10:51.840
<i>Let me tell you,</i>
<i>their leader was brave.</i>

10:53.120 --> 10:54.680
<i>He wouldn't leave</i>
<i>any of us behind,</i>

10:55.200 --> 10:57.000
<i>even though he was in danger.</i>

10:58.120 --> 11:02.000
<i>I only escaped thanks</i>
<i>to my superior grace and agility.</i>

11:05.080 --> 11:06.840
The leader is my dad.

11:07.120 --> 11:08.280
Who?

11:08.480 --> 11:09.600
Bron.

11:10.320 --> 11:12.480
Oh, yes, yes, that's him!

11:12.560 --> 11:13.920
Bron!

11:14.360 --> 11:16.080
What a brave Longneck he was.

11:16.160 --> 11:17.080
Ooh.

11:18.560 --> 11:20.360
Er... Is.
Uh, is!

11:20.440 --> 11:23.240
'Cause he's still is...
He still is... I'm sure.

11:23.920 --> 11:25.080
What happened to him?

11:25.680 --> 11:28.440
I don't know. I lost sight of him
at the Fire Mountain.

11:28.760 --> 11:30.120
He's in trouble?

11:30.200 --> 11:32.720
Grandpa, we have to help him.

11:33.320 --> 11:34.480
Littlefoot...

11:35.240 --> 11:37.200
Will you take us back there?

11:37.280 --> 11:38.520
You know the way.

11:39.840 --> 11:42.760
So, you want me to take you

11:42.880 --> 11:43.960
across the earthbreak,

11:44.000 --> 11:46.440
through the Land of the
Feather-Head Sharptooth,

11:46.560 --> 11:48.040
along the moving water

11:48.120 --> 11:51.440
back to the same Fire Mountain
that I just escaped from?

11:52.320 --> 11:55.120
How foolish do you think I look?

12:00.320 --> 12:01.960
Let me put it another way.

12:02.040 --> 12:04.240
The answer is no!

12:05.080 --> 12:08.880
Please. That's my dad.
He needs our help.

12:09.360 --> 12:12.360
He's right, Littlefoot.
We can't do it.

12:12.760 --> 12:14.240
But...

12:14.360 --> 12:16.160
You'll go, won't you?

12:23.920 --> 12:27.800
I'm sorry, Littlefoot.
It's too dangerous now.

12:28.600 --> 12:31.920
We must wait for the mountain
to stop spitting rocks.

12:32.120 --> 12:34.360
Bron wouldn't want us to get hurt.

12:34.720 --> 12:36.840
But my dad needs us now!

12:37.440 --> 12:40.880
Your father is very strong and wise.

12:40.920 --> 12:43.080
He's lived through
many earthshakes.

12:43.840 --> 12:46.640
I'm sure he's on his way
here right now.

13:06.720 --> 13:08.720
Where are you, Dad?

13:09.400 --> 13:10.920
CERA: There you are.

13:11.160 --> 13:13.240
We couldn't
find you anywhere.

13:13.320 --> 13:15.240
We all worry about you.

13:16.880 --> 13:18.680
We are sorry
about your father.

13:18.720 --> 13:20.120
Yes, we are.

13:20.760 --> 13:22.360
Yes, we sorry.

13:23.000 --> 13:24.280
Thanks.

13:24.320 --> 13:26.960
I think he's in trouble.
He needs me.

13:27.360 --> 13:28.640
What can you do?

13:29.120 --> 13:30.840
I'm going
to the Fire Mountain.

13:31.360 --> 13:33.160
I'm going to help him.

13:34.200 --> 13:36.600
(LAUGHING)
Oh, that funny,

13:36.680 --> 13:39.920
Petrie thought you say
you going to Fire Mountain.

13:40.000 --> 13:42.160
I... I did say that.
I'm going.

13:43.840 --> 13:45.800
No seem funny now.

13:46.440 --> 13:48.040
What are you talking about?

13:48.120 --> 13:50.040
You don't even know
how to get there.

13:50.480 --> 13:52.400
Wild Arms said how.

13:52.480 --> 13:55.800
Across the earthbreak,
through the Land of the
Feather-Head Sharpteeth

13:55.880 --> 13:58.200
and along the moving
water to the Fire Mountain.

13:58.600 --> 14:02.240
If you think
we're going to the
Fire Mountain...

14:02.320 --> 14:05.080
I don't.
He's my father.

14:05.560 --> 14:07.200
I'm going alone.

14:19.920 --> 14:21.120
(SQUAWKING)

14:26.040 --> 14:26.960
(GASPS)

14:30.360 --> 14:32.280
(ROARING IN DISTANCE)

14:32.440 --> 14:33.720
(TWIG SNAPS)

14:34.080 --> 14:36.080
(RUSTLING)
(GASPS)

14:37.440 --> 14:38.720
(PANTING)

14:44.480 --> 14:45.800
(GASPS)

15:02.000 --> 15:03.200
Guys?

15:03.520 --> 15:05.120
(ALL GASP)
PETRIE: Oh!

15:05.200 --> 15:07.080
Littlefoot,
you scare us.

15:07.920 --> 15:09.240
You scared me.

15:09.320 --> 15:11.080
What are you doing
out here?

15:11.640 --> 15:16.080
You cannot find
your dad all by yourself.
You cannot.

15:16.520 --> 15:18.360
Littlefoot need us.

15:18.400 --> 15:19.920
(MOANS)

15:20.000 --> 15:23.360
Uh-uh. It's too dangerous.
I can't let you come.

15:24.120 --> 15:25.880
You can't stop us.

16:00.600 --> 16:02.000
(LITTLEFOOT GASPS)

16:03.800 --> 16:07.160
Oh, looking down
make Petrie dizzy.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.080
(THUD)

16:10.680 --> 16:12.480
(ROARING IN DISTANCE)

16:17.120 --> 16:19.640
(NERVOUSLY)
What do we do now?

16:20.080 --> 16:22.480
Wild Arms said we have
to cross the earthbreak.

16:22.560 --> 16:24.200
Did he say how?

16:24.280 --> 16:25.560
No.

16:28.440 --> 16:30.360
We don't have
to go across!

16:31.040 --> 16:33.760
We can follow it
to the Long Valley.
(WIND HOWLING)

16:34.600 --> 16:36.840
That will bring us
to the Fire Mountain.

16:37.400 --> 16:40.320
Well, even
if the Long Valley
does go there,

16:40.400 --> 16:41.840
that will take longer.

16:42.680 --> 16:44.360
We've gotta cross now!

16:45.560 --> 16:46.480
(SCOFFS)

16:48.080 --> 16:50.680
Let me know
when you find a way.

16:56.720 --> 16:57.880
LITTLEFOOT: I know!

16:57.920 --> 17:01.040
If we can knock
this tree down,
we can use it to cross.

17:02.840 --> 17:03.800
Hmm.

17:05.040 --> 17:06.720
(STRAINING)

17:09.599 --> 17:10.839
(TREE TRUNK CREAKING)

17:10.960 --> 17:12.280
(STRAINING CONTINUES)

17:12.359 --> 17:13.720
(GROANS)

17:13.800 --> 17:15.920
I know it will reach

17:15.960 --> 17:18.119
if we could just...

17:18.200 --> 17:19.119
(STRAINING)

17:19.200 --> 17:20.440
CERA: Look out!

17:20.880 --> 17:21.839
(GASPS)

17:22.200 --> 17:23.640
(THUDS)
(GRUNTS)

17:24.040 --> 17:25.480
(TREE CREAKING)

17:27.560 --> 17:28.960
Yeah!

17:29.040 --> 17:30.360
(ALL CHEERING)

17:32.880 --> 17:34.040
Cera did it!

17:34.120 --> 17:35.480
(CLAPPING) Yes, she did!

17:37.120 --> 17:38.440
Thanks, Ducky.

17:39.000 --> 17:41.520
Well, if we're
gonna go, let's go!

18:11.560 --> 18:13.000
DUCKY: Now what?

18:13.560 --> 18:15.840
I guess we go there.

18:16.200 --> 18:20.320
But that's the Land
of the Feather-Head
Sharpteeth.

18:20.680 --> 18:22.880
It look scary.

18:23.400 --> 18:26.640
It will be okay.
Everything looks
scary to you.

18:26.680 --> 18:30.040
My nest not scary.
My... My tree
not scary.

18:30.120 --> 18:32.240
(DISTANT ROARING)

18:34.360 --> 18:36.440
(GULPS) That scary.

18:37.080 --> 18:38.600
We'll never
make it through!

18:38.680 --> 18:40.800
The Sharpteeth will
smell us coming.

18:41.280 --> 18:44.480
I think we should go back
and try the Long Valley.

18:44.560 --> 18:47.560
Petrie like any way
that's not that way.

18:48.000 --> 18:50.160
But this way's the fastest.

18:50.240 --> 18:53.080
If we go around,
we may be too late
to help my dad.

18:53.280 --> 18:56.240
If we get eaten,
we won't help him either.

18:56.720 --> 18:58.520
What do you think, Spike?

18:59.480 --> 19:00.640
Spike?

19:00.760 --> 19:02.080
(WIND HOWLING)

19:02.160 --> 19:03.880
CERA: Where's Spike?

19:04.280 --> 19:06.840
Oh! Sharptooth
ate Spike!

19:07.080 --> 19:09.400
I think Spike is
doing the eating.

19:09.800 --> 19:11.320
(YELLING) Spike!

19:12.440 --> 19:13.600
Spike?

19:14.360 --> 19:15.800
He can't have gone far.

19:18.520 --> 19:20.200
Where are you?

19:20.280 --> 19:22.000
Spike?

19:22.040 --> 19:23.440
Do you see him, Petrie?

19:24.560 --> 19:25.720
No.

19:27.480 --> 19:29.520
Spike!
(GASPS)

19:31.640 --> 19:32.960
Looks like he went this way.

19:37.640 --> 19:39.000
(FLIES BUZZING)

19:40.680 --> 19:42.040
Ew!

19:42.760 --> 19:46.040
Ugh. Petrie smell something not good.

19:46.080 --> 19:48.080
That's stinkweed.

19:48.160 --> 19:49.880
Yep, yep, yep.

19:50.600 --> 19:52.080
(SPIKE CHOMPING)

19:53.240 --> 19:54.680
(CHUCKLES)

19:54.720 --> 19:56.400
LITTLEFOOT: There you are.

19:56.800 --> 19:58.960
Spike, we don't have
time for this.

19:59.160 --> 20:03.200
My dad needs me.
No more food stops. Okay?

20:05.600 --> 20:08.920
Why did you eat
stinkweed, of all things?

20:11.760 --> 20:13.080
Ducky...

20:15.960 --> 20:17.200
(BURPS)

20:21.240 --> 20:23.000
(SINGING)
<i>Spike, you are my friend</i>

20:23.040 --> 20:24.920
<i>My very special friend</i>
(MOANS)

20:24.960 --> 20:27.280
<i>And we all like you very much</i>

20:28.440 --> 20:31.720
<i>We know that you are happy</i>
<i>when you fill up your tummy</i>

20:31.800 --> 20:35.480
<i>But what you are eating now</i>
<i>is not so yummy</i>
(MOANS)

20:35.520 --> 20:37.000
No, no, no!

20:37.080 --> 20:40.680
<i>It is hot and stinky</i>
<i>Stinky and hot</i>

20:41.120 --> 20:44.120
<i>It may feel good</i>
<i>inside your hungry spot</i>

20:44.200 --> 20:47.920
<i>But when you are eating things</i>
<i>that taste all mucky</i>

20:48.360 --> 20:51.600
<i>You will be smelling</i>
<i>very yuck-yuck-yucky</i>

20:51.640 --> 20:55.280
<i>So you should not</i>
<i>eat what is hot</i>

20:55.320 --> 20:57.240
<i>And stinky</i>

20:58.000 --> 20:59.160
(SNIFFS)

20:59.480 --> 21:00.840
Wait a minute.

21:01.680 --> 21:04.280
Spike, you just gave me an idea!

21:04.360 --> 21:06.280
(GRUNTS)

21:06.720 --> 21:10.040
Maybe there's a way to go
through the Sharptooth Land and be safe.

21:10.120 --> 21:11.960
That's impossible!

21:12.080 --> 21:14.280
But what if we cover
our smell with stinkweed?

21:14.480 --> 21:16.560
They'll smell that instead of us!

21:17.040 --> 21:18.960
You sure it work?

21:19.000 --> 21:22.080
Would you go near Spike,
smelling like that?

21:22.600 --> 21:25.960
Petrie would not go near
Petrie smelling like that!

21:26.040 --> 21:28.400
<i>Let's see if this will work</i>

21:28.560 --> 21:30.200
<i>I think this plan can work</i>

21:30.440 --> 21:32.440
<i>Yeah, because you're</i>
<i>always right</i>

21:32.520 --> 21:33.600
(SCOFFS)

21:33.920 --> 21:37.640
<i>If we're not lucky</i>
<i>and a Sharptooth meets us</i>

21:37.720 --> 21:41.360
<i>He think we stinkweed</i>
<i>and won't want to eats us</i>

21:41.440 --> 21:43.120
<i>Because we</i>

21:43.160 --> 21:46.280
ALL: <i>Hot and stinky</i>
<i>Stinky and hot</i>

21:47.000 --> 21:49.920
<i>We'll walk right past him</i>
<i>and we won't get caught</i>

21:50.680 --> 21:54.040
<i>He will not see us</i>
<i>with his big red eyes-es</i>

21:54.120 --> 21:57.400
<i>'Cause we be wearing</i>
<i>gooey green disguises</i>

21:57.520 --> 21:58.960
<i>No, he will not</i>

21:59.320 --> 22:01.080
<i>If we be hot</i>

22:01.440 --> 22:03.320
ALL: <i>And stinky</i>

22:06.800 --> 22:07.840
Your turn.

22:10.480 --> 22:11.680
ALL: <i>You've got to</i>
<i>got to be</i>

22:12.200 --> 22:14.760
<i>Hot and stinky</i>
<i>Stinky and hot</i>

22:15.680 --> 22:18.520
<i>You can all be goofy,</i>
<i>but I will not</i>

22:18.680 --> 22:22.680
<i>But that nasty Sharptooth</i>
<i>will smell you if you let it</i>

22:22.720 --> 22:25.960
<i>I don't like stinkweed</i>
<i>and I say forget it</i>

22:26.040 --> 22:27.600
BOTH: <i>No, you cannot</i>

22:27.680 --> 22:29.680
ALL: <i>You've got to,</i>
<i>got to, got to</i>

22:29.720 --> 22:31.760
<i>Got to, got to, got to,</i>
<i>got to be</i>

22:31.840 --> 22:33.000
<i>Hot and stinky</i>

22:33.400 --> 22:35.240
Hey, stop that!

22:35.680 --> 22:37.400
ALL: <i>Hot and stinky</i>

22:37.440 --> 22:38.840
Ew!

22:39.000 --> 22:41.240
ALL: <i>Hot and stinky</i>

22:41.360 --> 22:42.520
<i>Stinky and hot</i>

22:42.680 --> 22:45.000
<i>Now we all stinky</i>
<i>and hot</i>

22:45.320 --> 22:47.160
(LAUGHING)

22:49.120 --> 22:50.560
(BURPS)

22:51.440 --> 22:52.640
(GROANS)

22:55.480 --> 22:58.040
Okay, everybody, stay together.

22:58.640 --> 22:59.800
Here we go.

23:02.080 --> 23:04.320
CERA: I hope you know
what you're doing.

23:05.080 --> 23:06.320
LITTLEFOOT: Me, too.

23:09.240 --> 23:10.840
(GASPS)
(ROARING)

23:10.920 --> 23:12.360
(WHISPERS)
Get back, everyone.

23:13.400 --> 23:14.720
(FOOTSTEPS POUNDING)

23:14.880 --> 23:16.120
(ROARING)

23:20.480 --> 23:22.000
(GROWLING)

23:23.680 --> 23:24.920
(ROARING)

23:29.240 --> 23:31.880
(SOFTLY) Seems like
the stinkweed's working.

23:32.520 --> 23:33.840
Quiet, now.

23:34.360 --> 23:37.320
Yes, Petrie be very quiet,

23:37.400 --> 23:39.360
quieter than quiet,

23:39.440 --> 23:41.840
so quiet nobody hear me.

23:41.920 --> 23:43.000
(GROWLING)

23:43.400 --> 23:45.080
Petrie.
What?

23:45.400 --> 23:47.200
Oh, yes. Quiet.

23:48.360 --> 23:49.720
(SNIFFING)

23:50.960 --> 23:52.040
(GASPS)

23:55.120 --> 23:56.440
(SQUEAKING)

23:58.920 --> 24:00.000
(SCREAMS)

24:00.080 --> 24:01.040
(GROWLING)

24:02.840 --> 24:04.000
(ROARING)

24:15.160 --> 24:17.440
How much further, Littlefoot?

24:17.520 --> 24:19.160
I don't know!

24:19.800 --> 24:21.920
It's hot.
And I'm stinky!

24:22.000 --> 24:25.080
I don't like being hot and stinky!

24:25.280 --> 24:28.680
No one likes that.
No, no, no.

24:30.840 --> 24:32.440
Look! Water!

24:32.520 --> 24:33.480
(ALL EXCLAIM)

24:33.560 --> 24:34.680
CERA: Yeah!
DUCKY: Water!

24:34.760 --> 24:35.720
(ALL LAUGHING)

24:36.280 --> 24:37.320
(EXCLAIMS)

24:44.640 --> 24:47.480
Um, guys, maybe we should go soon.

24:48.000 --> 24:50.720
I'm not ready. My belly's
only half full,

24:50.840 --> 24:53.080
which means it's half empty.

24:53.120 --> 24:54.560
(GROANS)

24:55.240 --> 24:56.200
(MOANS)

24:58.360 --> 24:59.600
Spike.

24:59.840 --> 25:03.200
No eating the stinkweed.
We need to keep stinking.

25:06.440 --> 25:08.680
(STRUGGLING)
Spike, let go.

25:09.320 --> 25:10.880
Ahhh!
(SPLASHING)

25:14.640 --> 25:16.680
(CHUCKLES)
Littlefoot go for swim.

25:16.760 --> 25:17.840
I want to swim.

25:18.000 --> 25:18.960
No, Cera!

25:20.360 --> 25:22.520
Me, too.
(BOTH GIGGLE)

25:23.520 --> 25:25.600
(LAUGHING)

25:28.200 --> 25:29.680
(SNIFFING)

25:31.480 --> 25:32.840
(ROARS)

25:33.000 --> 25:34.320
(SNIFFS)

25:36.840 --> 25:37.880
(ROARS)

25:43.800 --> 25:45.440
(GIGGLING)

25:47.680 --> 25:50.880
Um, guys, the stinkweed...

25:52.000 --> 25:54.560
Stinkweed!
It's washing off!

25:54.640 --> 25:56.360
(ROARING)

25:58.520 --> 25:59.960
(SHUDDERS)

26:04.080 --> 26:05.240
(ROARS)

26:08.840 --> 26:10.120
(BOTH SNIFFING)

26:11.360 --> 26:12.640
(SHIVERING)

26:13.560 --> 26:14.960
(GROWLING)

26:15.680 --> 26:16.640
(ALL GASPING)

26:16.760 --> 26:17.680
(GROANS)

26:17.760 --> 26:19.160
(GROWLING)

26:19.240 --> 26:20.200
Run!

26:20.280 --> 26:21.200
(ROARS)

26:22.680 --> 26:24.040
Come on! Come on!

26:26.640 --> 26:27.760
Whoa!

26:28.440 --> 26:30.120
(ALL PANTING)

26:34.120 --> 26:35.320
(ROARING)

26:42.000 --> 26:43.040
(ROARING)

26:43.120 --> 26:44.800
(ALL WHIMPERING)

26:45.560 --> 26:47.720
(ALL SCREAMING)
(CRASHING)

26:48.160 --> 26:49.280
(GROWLING)

26:49.800 --> 26:51.240
(ROARING)

26:51.800 --> 26:53.360
(STRAINING)

26:56.160 --> 26:57.720
(ROARING)

26:58.680 --> 27:00.200
(ALL SCREAMING)

27:01.520 --> 27:03.160
(CRASHING)

27:07.920 --> 27:09.320
ALL: Whoa!

27:11.760 --> 27:13.200
This way!

27:13.560 --> 27:14.480
(ALL STRAINING)

27:28.920 --> 27:31.640
Come on! Come on!
(STRAINING CONTINUES)

27:33.320 --> 27:35.000
ALL: Whoa!

27:36.120 --> 27:37.400
(ALL GASP)

27:39.400 --> 27:40.760
We're trapped!

27:41.840 --> 27:43.480
We should have gone
my way!

27:43.560 --> 27:45.360
Cera, I'm trying
to think.

27:45.400 --> 27:46.680
(HUFFS)

27:50.840 --> 27:51.880
LITTLEFOOT: Hey!

27:52.440 --> 27:54.000
You all get behind those rocks.

27:54.080 --> 27:56.560
Spike, Cera, grab
each end of that vine.

28:01.800 --> 28:03.120
When I tell you,

28:03.160 --> 28:05.720
pull it tight. Okay?
ALL: Mmm-hmm.

28:06.320 --> 28:07.800
Here it come!

28:07.960 --> 28:09.720
(ROARING)

28:10.520 --> 28:13.000
Oh, no! This it!

28:13.120 --> 28:14.280
(GULPS)

28:16.440 --> 28:17.680
(GROWLS)

28:17.720 --> 28:19.280
(ROARS)

28:23.280 --> 28:25.760
Over here, big guy.
Right here.

28:27.000 --> 28:28.160
(ROARING)

28:28.240 --> 28:29.400
Now!

28:31.640 --> 28:32.920
(GROANING)

28:35.520 --> 28:37.000
(GROANING CONTINUES)

28:39.880 --> 28:41.160
(ROARS)

28:41.400 --> 28:42.800
(ALL CHEERING)

28:44.960 --> 28:46.200
(ROARING)

28:47.680 --> 28:48.920
(ROARS)
(ALL GASP)

28:49.000 --> 28:50.920
DUCKY: The other one
is coming!

28:51.200 --> 28:52.640
Let him come.

28:54.440 --> 28:55.400
(STRAINING)

28:56.560 --> 28:58.480
(CRASHING)

28:59.400 --> 29:00.760
(GROANING)

29:04.000 --> 29:05.240
(ALL CHEERING)

29:06.120 --> 29:07.480
(GROANS)

29:09.120 --> 29:10.520
CERA: Bye-bye!

29:13.200 --> 29:16.120
(SIGHS) We are all in one piece.

29:16.560 --> 29:19.320
(CHUCKLES)
Better than million little pieces.

29:19.360 --> 29:20.960
(RUMBLING)

29:23.320 --> 29:26.080
It's the Fire Mountain,
like Wild Arms said.

29:26.600 --> 29:30.040
We just have to reach
the moving water and we'll be fine.

29:30.400 --> 29:33.360
Fine? What do you mean, fine?

29:33.400 --> 29:36.280
We are nowhere near fine.

29:37.360 --> 29:38.600
(GROANS)

29:39.080 --> 29:40.440
Huh?

29:41.400 --> 29:42.360
(GASPS)

29:45.040 --> 29:48.400
DUCKY: Look, guys.
Spike found a way down.

29:50.240 --> 29:51.960
LITTLEFOOT: Thanks, Spike!

29:53.240 --> 29:55.360
(HOWLING)

30:03.320 --> 30:05.240
Well, hello there, Ruby and Chomper.

30:05.320 --> 30:07.000
What can we do for you?

30:07.080 --> 30:08.560
Is Littlefoot here?

30:09.760 --> 30:11.000
Did you look at Cera's?

30:11.480 --> 30:16.000
We've looked for him everywhere,
and everywhere we've looked, he isn't.

30:17.840 --> 30:20.040
I don't like the sound of this.

30:22.960 --> 30:24.680
(ROARING IN DISTANCE)

30:27.720 --> 30:29.760
(WHINING)

30:30.760 --> 30:35.840
(EXHALES) Petrie glad we leaving Land
of Feather-Head Sharpteeth.

30:36.280 --> 30:38.240
Until we have to go back home.

30:39.320 --> 30:40.320
Oh.

30:40.400 --> 30:42.560
Petrie stomach feel funny again.

30:44.680 --> 30:46.640
(YAWNS)

30:47.640 --> 30:49.560
(THUDS)
(SNORING)

30:55.120 --> 30:56.720
(SNORING CONTINUES)

30:57.760 --> 31:00.680
Come on, Spike.
We have to keep going.

31:01.440 --> 31:03.480
Spike is tired-ed, Littlefoot.

31:04.320 --> 31:06.720
Ducky, can you help move him?

31:10.760 --> 31:12.040
(SNORING CONTINUES)

31:12.120 --> 31:14.720
Okay, Spike, let's keep going.

31:14.800 --> 31:16.120
(STRAINING)

31:16.560 --> 31:17.760
(YAWNS)

31:20.440 --> 31:21.720
(SNORING RESUMES)

31:21.760 --> 31:23.000
(YAWNS)

31:26.200 --> 31:27.560
Ducky.

31:28.120 --> 31:29.400
(YAWNS)

31:29.480 --> 31:31.320
Nothing makes me tired

31:31.440 --> 31:34.320
like almost getting
eaten by Sharpteeth.

31:34.400 --> 31:35.880
(YAWNS)

31:39.800 --> 31:41.240
(YAWNS)

31:42.040 --> 31:43.920
Petrie so sorry.

31:44.000 --> 31:47.160
We find your dad tomorrow.

31:47.840 --> 31:49.280
(ALL SNORING)

31:54.880 --> 31:56.200
Littlefoot isn't here,

31:56.720 --> 31:58.840
and Cera should be home by now, too.

31:59.120 --> 32:01.360
I haven't seen Petrie either.

32:01.720 --> 32:05.040
Oh, dear. I assumed Spike
and Ducky were still out playing.

32:05.880 --> 32:07.480
I suspect the young ones

32:07.560 --> 32:09.720
have gone looking
for Littlefoot's father.

32:10.040 --> 32:11.120
Cera, too?

32:13.560 --> 32:15.200
(STOMPS)
What was she thinking?

32:15.280 --> 32:16.840
We have to find them right away.

32:17.720 --> 32:22.080
I saw Littlefoot listening closely
to what Wild Arms said.

32:22.160 --> 32:24.360
I would guess he went
the way he described.

32:26.200 --> 32:28.840
Thankfully, there's some light
from the night circle.

32:28.920 --> 32:30.360
We'll leave now.

32:30.440 --> 32:32.840
I'll ask Wild Arms to guide us.

32:36.440 --> 32:38.000
(SOFTLY)
We should go, too!

32:38.080 --> 32:41.440
(SOFTLY) Yes, but let's
not let them know we're going, too.

32:42.520 --> 32:44.240
(WIND HOWLING)

32:58.560 --> 32:59.960
(ROARING IN DISTANCE)
(SHUDDERS)

33:00.240 --> 33:01.560
(WHIMPERING)

33:02.920 --> 33:04.720
(ROARING CONTINUES)

33:06.360 --> 33:07.920
Okay, guys.
Ah... (CHUCKLES)

33:08.280 --> 33:10.520
I'm sure you can find
the Fire Mountain without me.

33:10.600 --> 33:11.960
I mean I'd love to come,

33:12.000 --> 33:14.960
but, uh, I got a thing
to do, and it's called

33:15.000 --> 33:16.800
"live."

33:17.880 --> 33:20.600
We need all the help
we can get, Wild Arms,

33:20.680 --> 33:23.520
with these little ones
out here all by themselves.

33:28.160 --> 33:31.320
Of all the wild stunts
these young ones have pulled,

33:31.360 --> 33:33.000
this is the worst.

33:33.080 --> 33:35.200
We'll find them,
Mr. Threehorn.

33:35.280 --> 33:37.080
We've got to.

33:50.520 --> 33:51.920
(ALL SNORING)

33:54.840 --> 33:56.280
(SIGHS)

34:02.800 --> 34:05.720
Through there is the Land
of the Feather-Head Sharpteeth.

34:06.360 --> 34:08.199
Right, Mr. Wild Arms?

34:08.280 --> 34:10.120
You mean the land of certain death?

34:10.400 --> 34:12.440
Yes, that is it.

34:12.520 --> 34:13.520
Okay?

34:14.199 --> 34:16.800
Or we can just be sensible

34:17.159 --> 34:18.639
and go back now.

34:18.960 --> 34:20.080
I vote sensible.

34:21.159 --> 34:22.520
Who's with me?

34:28.040 --> 34:31.800
I mean, come on. How do we even know
if the little ones came this way?

34:34.040 --> 34:36.000
Well, what do you think, Chomper?

34:37.280 --> 34:38.520
Chomper?

34:38.719 --> 34:41.080
I believe we have some followers.

34:41.159 --> 34:42.639
Chomper?

34:42.679 --> 34:44.000
Ruby?

34:44.600 --> 34:46.159
CHOMPER: I don't know
what you mean.

34:47.400 --> 34:48.880
We're not here.

34:49.440 --> 34:51.800
It's okay.
Come on out.

34:55.679 --> 34:59.040
Hello, everybody, everybody, hello.

34:59.160 --> 35:00.200
Hi.

35:00.920 --> 35:03.440
(SCREAMS) Sharptooth!

35:04.560 --> 35:06.640
Run! Save yourself!

35:08.280 --> 35:09.520
(SHUDDERING)

35:09.560 --> 35:12.440
(CHUCKLES) No need
for panic, Mr. Wild Arms.

35:12.520 --> 35:14.840
Chomper here is a friend.

35:17.320 --> 35:20.000
Uh, have you taken
a good look at his teeth?

35:20.280 --> 35:22.320
(CHUCKLES) It's all right,
Mr. Wild Arms.

35:22.400 --> 35:23.960
Chomper only eats bugs.

35:26.160 --> 35:28.040
We don't need another Sharptooth

35:28.120 --> 35:31.280
when we're walking into
a whole land of Sharpteeth.

35:31.840 --> 35:34.800
Oh, finally someone who's sensible!

35:35.520 --> 35:36.920
Up top!

35:38.520 --> 35:39.840
Okay.

35:41.000 --> 35:44.120
Four more eyes are four
more chances to find them.

35:44.240 --> 35:45.400
Please?

35:47.560 --> 35:48.960
(SIGHS)

35:49.040 --> 35:50.160
Well,

35:50.240 --> 35:53.200
guess we can't just send
you two back on your own.

35:54.160 --> 35:55.800
BOTH: Yay!

35:55.880 --> 35:57.400
(BOTH CHEERING)

35:58.360 --> 36:00.040
Hey, Mr. Wild Arms.

36:01.520 --> 36:02.880
(EXHALES)

36:05.800 --> 36:07.480
(LAUGHS)
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

36:07.600 --> 36:09.760
Would you mind, Mr. Threehorn?

36:10.720 --> 36:14.120
I knew I'd end up carrying him
sooner or later.

36:14.960 --> 36:16.680
(WILD ARMS GROANING)

36:18.960 --> 36:23.320
Chomper, can you smell if Littlefoot
and the others went this way?

36:23.760 --> 36:24.920
Uh-huh.

36:26.720 --> 36:29.400
(SNIFFING)
Littlefoot. Cera.

36:31.120 --> 36:32.560
I smell them all.

36:32.800 --> 36:34.520
Come on, through here.

36:36.240 --> 36:37.520
(SNIFFING)

36:45.640 --> 36:48.760
CERA: You said we'd find
the moving water by now.

36:50.240 --> 36:52.080
It should be around the bend.

36:52.120 --> 36:55.000
That's what you said two bends ago!

36:56.120 --> 36:57.360
(STOMACH GROWLING)

36:57.400 --> 36:59.520
(GASPS)
Sharpteeth!

37:00.280 --> 37:03.200
Do not worry, Petrie,
that is just Spike's belly.

37:04.280 --> 37:06.680
Oh. (SIGHS)

37:08.440 --> 37:09.720
(CHUCKLES)

37:10.600 --> 37:13.720
We're all hungry!
And thirsty!

37:17.600 --> 37:19.400
I have an idea.

37:19.480 --> 37:22.120
I'm going to go up there
and look around.

37:22.200 --> 37:23.320
You all wait here.

37:24.960 --> 37:26.080
Hmm.

37:38.200 --> 37:40.640
LITTLEFOOT: I see it!
The Fire Mountain.

37:40.720 --> 37:43.280
And there, the moving water
leads right to it.

37:45.360 --> 37:47.800
But how come
we can't find it?

37:50.440 --> 37:51.600
(GASPS)

37:55.800 --> 37:57.360
Can I see, Littlefoot?

37:57.720 --> 37:59.840
Um, uh...

38:00.080 --> 38:01.400
(GASPS)
Spike?

38:02.200 --> 38:04.720
I don't know
if you should come up here.

38:04.760 --> 38:05.960
Oh!

38:06.040 --> 38:07.800
Petrie want to see, too.

38:07.880 --> 38:09.360
CERA: Hey, wait for me.
Um...

38:09.800 --> 38:12.560
I think this ledge is too small
to hold all of us.

38:12.680 --> 38:14.640
I want to see for myself.

38:14.680 --> 38:16.360
Cera...
(SIGHS)

38:16.440 --> 38:18.800
We're nowhere near the moving water.

38:19.120 --> 38:20.280
It should be around...

38:20.360 --> 38:22.040
"Around the bend."

38:22.080 --> 38:24.040
I don't think you know
where we're going.

38:24.120 --> 38:26.120
We should have gone my way!

38:26.200 --> 38:27.160
(THUDDING)
(ALL GASP)

38:27.240 --> 38:28.520
(CRACKING)

38:29.240 --> 38:30.400
Oops.

38:30.920 --> 38:32.280
(ALL SCREAMING)

38:43.400 --> 38:45.080
(ALL GRUNTING)

38:45.880 --> 38:47.920
(MUFFLED STRAINING)
(GROANS)

38:51.040 --> 38:52.000
(GASPS)

38:53.520 --> 38:55.160
(GRUNTING)

38:55.280 --> 38:57.560
Nice going, Littlefoot!

38:58.520 --> 39:00.800
Me? I told you not to come up there!

39:01.240 --> 39:03.000
None of this would have happened

39:03.080 --> 39:05.240
if we went through the Long Valley,
like I said.

39:05.480 --> 39:09.080
If we went on instead of stopping
last night I'd be with my dad!

39:10.040 --> 39:12.640
You wouldn't be anywhere without me.

39:13.560 --> 39:16.000
You? You're just slowing me down.

39:17.240 --> 39:18.600
You all are.

39:18.760 --> 39:20.240
(ALL GASPING)

39:21.480 --> 39:23.120
I'd be better off alone.

39:24.720 --> 39:27.440
You want to be alone, that's fine!

39:27.920 --> 39:28.960
Fine!

39:31.600 --> 39:34.080
I'm gonna find the Long Valley.

39:34.160 --> 39:36.480
I know where that will lead.

39:39.120 --> 39:40.880
You coming with me?

39:45.600 --> 39:46.920
(GROANS SADLY)

39:47.000 --> 39:48.080
Good.

39:48.880 --> 39:50.400
We're better off without him.

40:00.600 --> 40:04.160
(SINGING)
<i>Who needs friends to slow you down</i>

40:04.240 --> 40:07.640
<i>Wasting our time</i>
<i>with too much talking</i>

40:08.120 --> 40:11.600
<i>Who needs friends to grumble and frown</i>
(SQUEAKING)

40:12.200 --> 40:15.120
<i>When we should just keep walking</i>

40:15.800 --> 40:18.760
<i>I'm just fine</i>

40:18.840 --> 40:21.240
<i>On my own</i>

40:22.120 --> 40:23.160
(GASPS)

40:23.240 --> 40:26.800
<i>I will be better off alone</i>

40:29.880 --> 40:33.040
<i>Who needs friends who get you lost</i>

40:33.440 --> 40:37.080
<i>And don't wanna listen</i>
<i>when you tell them</i>

40:37.200 --> 40:40.920
<i>That you know the best way to go</i>

40:41.360 --> 40:45.040
<i>And you're just trying to help them</i>

40:45.400 --> 40:47.720
<i>Might as well</i>

40:48.600 --> 40:50.840
<i>Talk to this stone</i>

40:51.480 --> 40:52.400
Ow!

40:52.480 --> 40:56.000
<i>I'm sure I'm better off alone</i>

40:58.760 --> 41:00.800
<i>And who needs friends</i>
<i>Who needs friends</i>

41:00.880 --> 41:03.120
<i>To boss me around</i>
<i>To boss me around</i>

41:03.320 --> 41:06.280
BOTH: <i>That's really hard to swallow</i>

41:06.520 --> 41:08.120
<i>Can't she see?</i>
<i>Can't he see?</i>

41:08.200 --> 41:10.280
<i>It's so clear to me</i>
<i>It's so clear to me</i>

41:10.440 --> 41:11.600
BOTH: <i>I should lead...</i>

41:11.680 --> 41:13.680
<i>And she should follow?</i>
<i>And he should follow?</i>

41:14.280 --> 41:17.320
BOTH: <i>My mistake</i>

41:17.880 --> 41:19.640
<i>I should have known</i>

41:21.560 --> 41:25.040
<i>I would be better off alone</i>

41:28.920 --> 41:32.480
<i>I'm sure I'm better off alone</i>

41:32.560 --> 41:36.160
<i>We're so much better off alone</i>

41:37.000 --> 41:38.680
<i>I guess</i>

41:38.760 --> 41:42.520
<i>I'm better off alone</i>

41:52.560 --> 41:53.760
(WIND WHOOSHING)

41:54.840 --> 41:55.840
Huh?

42:03.400 --> 42:05.560
It's too soon to be dark.

42:06.280 --> 42:07.240
(GASPS)

42:07.800 --> 42:10.160
Oh, no!
Sand cloud!

42:14.360 --> 42:16.400
Cera? Guys?

42:23.720 --> 42:26.840
(GROANS)
Petrie feel bad.

42:27.040 --> 42:28.760
(MOANS IN AGREEMENT)

42:29.480 --> 42:32.120
Spike, too.
Me, three.

42:33.400 --> 42:34.960
I miss Littlefoot.

42:36.120 --> 42:37.840
(WIND WHOOSHING)

42:40.440 --> 42:42.440
Petrie hate wind!

42:42.960 --> 42:43.920
(YELLS)

42:44.080 --> 42:45.120
(GASPS) Petrie!

42:45.360 --> 42:47.320
Help!

42:48.960 --> 42:51.160
Hurry, Spike.
Hurry.

42:51.840 --> 42:52.800
(GASPS)

42:56.320 --> 42:57.400
Guys?

42:57.480 --> 42:58.560
(GASPING)

43:00.840 --> 43:02.160
Sand cloud!

43:08.080 --> 43:09.040
(GASPS)

43:21.720 --> 43:25.200
ETTA: Don't tell me you're thinking
about going back out there.

43:26.440 --> 43:28.920
That's a sand cloud,
case you didn't notice.

43:29.720 --> 43:31.120
My friends are out there!

43:31.160 --> 43:34.400
Well, then you'd best hope
they find some shelter like you.

43:34.960 --> 43:36.680
You don't understand.

43:37.120 --> 43:39.160
They're only out here because of me.

43:39.960 --> 43:43.360
Well, getting yourself killed is not
a way I ever heard of showing you care.

43:44.160 --> 43:46.800
Nothing you can do
but wait out the storm.

43:52.720 --> 43:54.000
(GROWLING)

43:59.520 --> 44:00.520
Mmm.

44:05.800 --> 44:07.400
Nope, not dead.

44:07.880 --> 44:10.920
You still got time
to grow up and learn to listen.

44:11.000 --> 44:12.320
(SIGHS)

44:12.400 --> 44:13.800
(GROANS)

44:23.920 --> 44:25.520
(LEAVES RUSTLING)

44:28.440 --> 44:29.720
(GRUNTING)

44:31.440 --> 44:32.840
(SPLUTTERING)

44:36.360 --> 44:37.520
Ducky?

44:38.680 --> 44:40.080
Spike?

44:40.160 --> 44:41.360
Petrie?

44:42.200 --> 44:43.320
(GASPS)

44:44.520 --> 44:46.040
Who's there?

44:46.280 --> 44:47.520
(BOTH GASPING)

44:48.480 --> 44:49.880
(BOTH SIGHING)

44:50.400 --> 44:52.000
(SIGHS) Spike.

44:52.320 --> 44:54.760
What are you doing sneaking up on me?

44:55.000 --> 44:56.440
Where's Ducky?

44:56.920 --> 44:58.480
(BOTH GASPING)

45:00.200 --> 45:01.880
(SPLUTTERING)

45:02.760 --> 45:04.040
Here I am.

45:04.880 --> 45:06.920
Good.
What about Petrie?

45:07.640 --> 45:09.680
The wind tooked him away.

45:10.440 --> 45:11.720
Oh, great!

45:12.160 --> 45:14.440
I guess we'll have to look for him.

45:15.240 --> 45:17.000
What about Littlefoot?

45:17.800 --> 45:20.240
He's probably far off by now.

45:20.600 --> 45:22.640
I'll bet he missed the storm.

45:23.320 --> 45:24.840
I do not know.

45:25.720 --> 45:27.000
Well, I do.

45:27.440 --> 45:29.160
Let's go find Petrie.

45:29.520 --> 45:32.120
The storm covereded
everything with sand.

45:32.720 --> 45:34.120
Which way?

45:34.200 --> 45:35.880
(MOANS IN AGREEMENT)

45:39.800 --> 45:41.360
Um, that way.

45:44.000 --> 45:45.920
I do not think that's right.

45:46.000 --> 45:47.320
No, no, no.

45:48.000 --> 45:50.680
Well, I say it is.
Come on.

45:57.400 --> 45:59.440
Petrie! Petrie!

46:00.840 --> 46:02.800
Where is he?

46:06.480 --> 46:07.840
(SHIVERING)

46:12.920 --> 46:14.040
Ducky?

46:14.560 --> 46:16.080
Spike?

46:16.160 --> 46:17.360
Anybody?

46:17.400 --> 46:20.280
(SHOUTING)
Anybody at all?

46:24.960 --> 46:26.120
(GASPS)

46:27.880 --> 46:29.360
(WHIMPERS)

46:29.400 --> 46:31.440
Littlefoot! Cera!

46:31.520 --> 46:33.080
(SCREAMING) Help!

46:38.920 --> 46:39.920
(WHIMPERS)

46:40.880 --> 46:42.200
Nice diggers.

46:42.360 --> 46:44.560
Nice diggers.
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

46:44.920 --> 46:46.360
(WHIMPERS)

46:52.440 --> 46:53.920
(WHIMPERS)

46:55.480 --> 46:56.760
No!

46:57.240 --> 46:58.440
(GRUNTS)

46:59.400 --> 47:01.520
No eat Petrie!

47:11.000 --> 47:12.160
ALL: More.

47:13.120 --> 47:15.560
(GULPING) More?

47:16.080 --> 47:17.200
ALL: More.

47:18.200 --> 47:19.480
More?

47:20.160 --> 47:23.000
ALL: More. More. More.

47:33.520 --> 47:35.080
(ALL CHEERING)

47:39.640 --> 47:41.560
Hello.
(LAUGHS NERVOUSLY)

47:41.600 --> 47:43.440
Me Petrie.

47:43.480 --> 47:46.320
ALL: Petrie!
Petrie! Petrie!

47:53.880 --> 47:55.160
Whatcha doin', hon?

47:55.600 --> 47:57.640
I'm gonna go help my friends.

47:58.400 --> 48:00.000
Aren't you nice.

48:00.080 --> 48:02.360
You know, I had a cousin
who was nice like that.

48:03.160 --> 48:07.040
She put her head in the mouth
of a Sharptooth just to help a friend.

48:07.120 --> 48:09.200
Course, she's not
around anymore, 'cause...

48:09.240 --> 48:11.600
Well, she put her head
in the mouth of a Sharptooth.

48:11.640 --> 48:12.760
(LAUGHS)

48:15.600 --> 48:18.480
Oh! I'm Etta, by the way.
What's your name?

48:18.520 --> 48:19.760
Littlefoot.

48:21.920 --> 48:24.440
Sorry.
Nice to meet you, Fiddlefoot.

48:25.160 --> 48:28.560
You don't mind me saying,
you look more like a Littlefoot.

48:29.720 --> 48:31.680
That's what I'm gonna call you.

48:32.120 --> 48:33.680
Nice to meet you, Etta.

48:37.560 --> 48:38.600
Look, Etta!

48:39.720 --> 48:41.120
Daylight!

48:41.240 --> 48:42.520
(RUMBLING)
What?

48:43.240 --> 48:44.920
Earthshake!

48:44.960 --> 48:46.280
Whoa!

48:46.600 --> 48:47.640
Etta!

48:48.920 --> 48:50.240
(CRASHING)

48:56.920 --> 48:57.880
(BOTH GASP)

48:58.520 --> 49:00.680
(SIGHS)
That was a close one.

49:00.760 --> 49:02.960
The opening.
We gotta move this.

49:03.000 --> 49:04.840
(BOTH STRAINING)

49:07.280 --> 49:10.240
Looks like we're good and stuck.

49:12.160 --> 49:13.480
(SIGHS)

49:14.560 --> 49:15.960
CERA: Petrie!

49:19.480 --> 49:20.960
Petrie!

49:21.840 --> 49:23.360
(MOANS)

49:24.840 --> 49:28.240
Hmm.
Are you sure this is the right way?

49:31.320 --> 49:33.120
Look! Footprints!

49:33.520 --> 49:35.440
Now we're getting somewhere!

49:35.520 --> 49:36.680
Hmm.

49:37.480 --> 49:39.560
But that's Spike's footprint.

49:39.800 --> 49:41.080
And yours.

49:41.160 --> 49:43.600
Oh, you just led us in a circle.

49:44.360 --> 49:45.520
Oh.

49:45.600 --> 49:48.040
Well, maybe I meant to do that.

49:48.520 --> 49:50.040
(GASPS)

49:50.840 --> 49:52.760
(STUTTERING)
What's going on?

49:54.200 --> 49:56.080
Hey! Get away!

50:04.520 --> 50:06.360
Big dinner for leader!

50:06.440 --> 50:07.800
(GASPS)

50:08.880 --> 50:10.200
Get leader!

50:10.360 --> 50:13.600
ALL: Leader!
Leader! Leader!

50:14.080 --> 50:17.040
(STAMMERING)
I'm not afraid of your silly old leader.

50:17.360 --> 50:19.120
Here come leader!

50:27.000 --> 50:27.960
(BOTH GASP)

50:30.640 --> 50:32.240
Petrie!
We found you!

50:33.400 --> 50:34.440
Huh?

50:34.720 --> 50:36.440
(MOANS EXCITEDLY)

50:37.000 --> 50:40.000
(SIGHING)
Petrie so glad to see you.

50:40.520 --> 50:41.560
You?

50:42.000 --> 50:44.040
You can't be their leader!

50:44.480 --> 50:47.720
ALL: (CHANTING)
Petrie! Petrie! Petrie!

50:48.480 --> 50:51.160
(CHUCKLES)
Me think me can.

50:51.640 --> 50:54.640
You don't even know
how to be a leader.

50:55.160 --> 50:56.880
Oh, it no hard.

50:56.920 --> 50:58.120
Watch.

51:07.920 --> 51:10.440
ALL: (CHANTING) Leader!
Leader! Leader!

51:11.480 --> 51:12.560
Huh?

51:12.600 --> 51:14.960
I wish Littlefoot could see this.

51:15.840 --> 51:17.200
No find yet?

51:17.400 --> 51:18.880
(MOANS SADLY)

51:19.400 --> 51:21.920
He's probably
at the Fire Mountain by now.

51:23.080 --> 51:25.280
(GRUNTING)

51:25.880 --> 51:27.160
(SIGHS)

51:28.440 --> 51:30.560
We should find the Long Valley.

51:31.000 --> 51:32.840
What do you think we should do?

51:32.920 --> 51:34.600
I just told you.

51:34.680 --> 51:36.360
I mean Petrie.

51:36.960 --> 51:39.000
Who cares what Petrie thinks?

51:40.040 --> 51:42.640
ALL: (CHANTING) Petrie!
Petrie! Petrie!

51:43.320 --> 51:44.600
They care.

51:45.320 --> 51:46.360
Well?

51:47.160 --> 51:48.880
Petrie think...

51:49.000 --> 51:52.280
Well, Petrie think, um...

51:53.000 --> 51:54.440
We're waiting!

51:55.440 --> 51:57.480
Uh, being leader hard.

51:57.920 --> 52:00.760
(SIGHS)
But Petrie miss Littlefoot.

52:01.200 --> 52:02.840
(MOANS IN AGREEMENT)

52:02.920 --> 52:05.040
Us, too.
Yep, yep, yep.

52:05.480 --> 52:08.080
Well, how are you
supposed to find him?

52:08.400 --> 52:10.200
We don't even know where we are!

52:11.640 --> 52:13.160
So we are lost.

52:13.880 --> 52:15.680
(GULPS)
No, no, we're not.

52:15.800 --> 52:17.600
I mean, not really.

52:20.760 --> 52:22.880
Okay, we are lost.

52:24.120 --> 52:26.840
And I miss him, too.

52:28.600 --> 52:30.160
Let's go find him.

52:36.400 --> 52:38.800
Petrie must go
and find friend.

52:39.640 --> 52:41.440
ALL: No! No! No!

52:42.200 --> 52:43.640
No be sad.

52:45.280 --> 52:48.840
Um...
Petrie order no be sad.

52:51.520 --> 52:53.680
Petrie always remember you.

52:54.040 --> 52:55.320
And you.

52:55.400 --> 52:58.000
And back there, all you.

53:03.320 --> 53:05.520
ALL: Petrie! Petrie!

53:05.720 --> 53:07.280
Petrie!

53:07.360 --> 53:08.320
(RUSTLING)

53:10.600 --> 53:12.400
ALL: Oh!
(LAUGHING)

53:14.040 --> 53:16.400
Leader! Leader! Leader!

53:16.760 --> 53:18.280
(CHEERING) Yay!

53:19.560 --> 53:20.960
(SPIKE GROANS)

53:27.640 --> 53:28.680
(LITTLEFOOT GRUNTING)

53:29.600 --> 53:31.360
Littlefoot, leave it be.

53:31.440 --> 53:33.640
Honey, no one can break through that.

53:34.200 --> 53:35.560
Cera could.

53:35.800 --> 53:37.240
But she's not here.

53:37.560 --> 53:39.600
(SIGHS) It's hopeless.

53:41.480 --> 53:43.640
Come on, Littlefoot, cheer up.

53:43.680 --> 53:45.680
I had a sister once used to say,

53:45.720 --> 53:47.640
"Just when things get darkest,"

53:47.720 --> 53:49.680
"that's when you look for the light."

53:51.080 --> 53:53.320
Unless, of course,
it's too dark to find it.

53:53.840 --> 53:55.520
You don't understand.

53:55.600 --> 53:58.160
My friends only came out here
to help me find my dad.

53:58.760 --> 54:00.440
And now I can't save him.

54:01.200 --> 54:03.480
Well, what...
What happened to your dad?

54:04.920 --> 54:08.280
He got trapped by an earthshake
when the Fire Mountain blew up.

54:09.320 --> 54:10.960
That's what Wild Arms said.

54:11.680 --> 54:14.640
Wild Arms?
Oh, heck, I know a Wild Arms.

54:14.960 --> 54:16.800
Moves like this?

54:18.200 --> 54:19.720
Yes, that's him!

54:20.280 --> 54:22.000
He travels with my dad's herd.

54:22.600 --> 54:24.360
They all made it out okay,

54:24.440 --> 54:25.720
except my dad.

54:26.200 --> 54:27.400
Oh, my.

54:28.080 --> 54:29.760
Is your father's name Bron?

54:30.080 --> 54:31.600
Yeah, it is!

54:32.120 --> 54:34.400
Oh, honey, I was there,
at Fire Mountain.

54:34.480 --> 54:36.720
What happened?
Please tell me.

54:37.560 --> 54:38.760
Okay.

54:39.320 --> 54:41.160
But you may not like it.

54:43.720 --> 54:46.520
<i>The Fire Mountain</i>
<i>was shaking and rumbling.</i>

54:46.600 --> 54:49.040
<i>Trouble was coming</i>
<i>and everybody knew it.</i>

54:49.640 --> 54:53.720
<i>There was only one longneck who knew</i>
<i>what to do and that was your dad.</i>

54:54.200 --> 54:57.720
<i>He ordered the herd to head down</i>
<i>the mountain as fast as they could.</i>

54:58.360 --> 55:01.000
<i>But the Fire Mountain</i>
<i>didn't wait for them to get down.</i>

55:01.920 --> 55:04.000
(EXPLODING)

55:04.920 --> 55:06.360
Ow!

55:07.960 --> 55:10.200
<i>I barely made it out myself.</i>

55:16.200 --> 55:18.880
<i>Someone fell.</i>
<i>I think it was Wild Arms.</i>

55:21.160 --> 55:23.120
<i>Your father went back</i>
<i>and saved him.</i>

55:28.560 --> 55:30.200
<i>And that's when it happened.</i>

55:31.480 --> 55:33.360
<i>There was an explosion.</i>

55:34.800 --> 55:37.280
<i>Your father got separated</i>
<i>from the others.</i>

55:40.360 --> 55:42.480
Well, honey,
that's the last I saw of him.

55:44.960 --> 55:46.480
That's my dad.

55:47.520 --> 55:49.480
He wouldn't leave anyone behind.

55:50.080 --> 55:52.080
Even though it meant
risking his life.

55:54.840 --> 55:57.360
I guess that's what
you do for your herd.

55:59.320 --> 56:01.040
And your friends.

56:01.640 --> 56:03.560
I never should have left them.

56:04.640 --> 56:06.320
Now, Littlefoot,

56:06.880 --> 56:08.240
don't give up.

56:08.360 --> 56:11.920
Get off your tail
and we're gonna get out of this cave.

56:13.360 --> 56:14.560
How?

56:15.520 --> 56:20.520
(SINGING) <i>When you're stuck in a hole</i>
<i>and you don't know where to go</i>

56:21.080 --> 56:26.000
<i>When it's too dark for you to tell</i>
<i>Your tail from your toe</i>

56:26.840 --> 56:30.440
<i>You wonder which way is wrong</i>

56:30.520 --> 56:32.760
<i>And which road is right?</i>

56:34.520 --> 56:38.320
<i>The best thing</i>
<i>for you to do is just</i>

56:38.360 --> 56:40.920
<i>Look for the light</i>

56:48.080 --> 56:49.920
<i>Look for the light</i>

56:50.040 --> 56:51.520
<i>One little spark</i>

56:51.840 --> 56:55.360
<i>A little bit of hope</i>
<i>to lead you out of the dark</i>

56:55.800 --> 57:00.080
<i>Somewhere deep inside of you,</i>
<i>it's shining so bright</i>

57:01.520 --> 57:04.560
<i>All you gotta do is look</i>

57:04.720 --> 57:08.200
<i>You gotta look for the light</i>

57:09.160 --> 57:12.720
<i>If there's a wall,</i>
<i>sometimes you bump it</i>

57:13.400 --> 57:16.680
<i>A big old rock, you have to jump it</i>

57:16.920 --> 57:19.920
<i>Maybe you're tired</i>
<i>Maybe you're scared</i>

57:20.000 --> 57:20.960
(GASPS)

57:21.080 --> 57:24.160
<i>But the only thing you have to be</i>

57:24.320 --> 57:27.760
<i>Is be prepared</i>

57:28.280 --> 57:30.240
<i>To look for the light</i>

57:30.360 --> 57:32.120
<i>And open your eyes</i>

57:32.200 --> 57:35.640
<i>You never know when</i>
<i>you're gonna find a surprise</i>

57:36.040 --> 57:37.760
<i>Some things may tickle you</i>
(GIGGLING)

57:38.040 --> 57:39.720
<i>Others may bite</i>

57:41.640 --> 57:44.800
<i>So, listen to my sister,</i>
<i>mister</i>

57:44.880 --> 57:47.720
<i>Come on and look for the light</i>

57:48.840 --> 57:51.920
<i>Get up and look for the light</i>

57:52.160 --> 57:55.160
<i>Get up</i>
<i>and look for the light</i>

57:56.520 --> 57:59.800
<i>Come on and look for the light</i>

58:05.200 --> 58:07.320
Well, that's what my
sister used to say,

58:07.400 --> 58:09.520
but you can't exactly go by her.

58:09.600 --> 58:12.960
She ran into a tree once and been
a little funny in the head ever since.

58:15.800 --> 58:18.440
Hey, Etta!
Maybe that's a way out!

58:25.720 --> 58:29.360
(SIGHS)
It's just light shining off the water.

58:29.960 --> 58:32.120
Oh, I'm sorry, Littlefoot.

58:33.000 --> 58:34.560
(SIGHS)

58:35.160 --> 58:36.800
That's okay.

58:37.320 --> 58:39.160
Let's keep looking for the light.

58:40.040 --> 58:42.040
That's the spirit!

58:47.480 --> 58:48.920
It's water, Etta!

58:49.160 --> 58:50.560
Heard ya the first time,

58:50.680 --> 58:52.520
but we're looking for a way out.

58:52.600 --> 58:54.080
Like I was saying about my sister...

58:54.400 --> 58:57.160
Etta, if water's coming in the cave,

58:57.240 --> 58:58.320
you know what that means?

58:58.840 --> 59:00.040
It's wet?

59:00.400 --> 59:03.320
No. It means it has to be
going out, too!

59:03.400 --> 59:06.480
If it wasn't, the cave would be
filled with water.

59:06.920 --> 59:09.080
Oh, I didn't think of that.

59:09.520 --> 59:11.240
If water can find a way out,

59:11.320 --> 59:12.640
maybe we can, too!

59:13.960 --> 59:16.760
I like the way you think, Littlefoot!

59:18.440 --> 59:20.720
She had a lot of sayings,
my sister. Like...

59:20.760 --> 59:23.200
You know, "Don't use your tail
to sniff the trail."

59:23.280 --> 59:24.920
(LAUGHING)

59:25.000 --> 59:26.600
Oh, that got me every time.

59:26.680 --> 59:28.080
(MUMBLING)

59:30.560 --> 59:32.360
Littlefoot!

59:33.240 --> 59:34.680
Littlefoot!

59:34.920 --> 59:36.520
Littlefoot!

59:40.680 --> 59:42.800
Littlefoot!

59:45.000 --> 59:47.960
(MOANS EXCITEDLY)
Hmm!

59:48.360 --> 59:50.920
Oh! Look!
Littlefoot's footprints!

59:51.280 --> 59:53.680
He must be close, yes, yes, yes!

59:54.040 --> 59:55.800
Nice going, Spike!

59:55.880 --> 59:59.240
That was hard to see with all these
Sharptooth footprints around.

59:59.480 --> 01:00:01.400
Sharptooth?
(GROWLING)

01:00:01.480 --> 01:00:02.560
(ALL GASPING)

01:00:02.640 --> 01:00:04.200
(ROARING)

01:00:04.440 --> 01:00:05.880
(SCREAMING)

01:00:14.320 --> 01:00:15.480
CERA: This way!

01:00:19.080 --> 01:00:20.480
(GROWLING)

01:00:24.680 --> 01:00:25.800
(SCREAMING)

01:00:26.760 --> 01:00:27.920
(SHUDDERING)

01:00:28.040 --> 01:00:29.400
(GROWLING)

01:00:31.840 --> 01:00:33.240
(ROARING)

01:00:38.360 --> 01:00:40.200
(GASPS) Look, Etta.

01:00:41.080 --> 01:00:42.840
It's the moving water!

01:00:43.120 --> 01:00:44.920
My friends and I were looking for it.

01:00:45.240 --> 01:00:46.600
Oh, my.

01:00:46.720 --> 01:00:48.200
It's under the ground!

01:00:48.280 --> 01:00:50.320
That's why we couldn't
find it before.

01:00:53.240 --> 01:00:55.280
I bet if we follow this water,

01:00:55.360 --> 01:00:57.360
it will lead right
to the Fire Mountain.

01:00:58.760 --> 01:01:01.400
Now all we have to do
is find my friends.

01:01:01.880 --> 01:01:03.440
Hmm. But how?

01:01:03.560 --> 01:01:05.080
They could be anywhere.

01:01:08.040 --> 01:01:09.400
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

01:01:09.800 --> 01:01:12.680
That's funny.
It's like I can hear them.

01:01:13.880 --> 01:01:15.280
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

01:01:17.040 --> 01:01:18.840
Etta, can you get up there?

01:01:20.160 --> 01:01:21.720
Hmm.

01:01:21.840 --> 01:01:23.640
My wing got a little singed.

01:01:23.720 --> 01:01:25.080
But I can try.

01:01:28.120 --> 01:01:30.160
(HUMMING)

01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:38.680
Hmm.

01:01:40.240 --> 01:01:41.200
Now what?

01:01:41.560 --> 01:01:42.760
Poke through!

01:01:43.480 --> 01:01:44.880
Okay.

01:01:45.560 --> 01:01:46.600
(THUDDING)

01:01:53.400 --> 01:01:54.400
(SHUDDERING)

01:01:54.520 --> 01:01:55.440
ETTA: Yoo-hoo.

01:01:55.520 --> 01:01:56.560
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:01:57.360 --> 01:01:59.200
(LAUGHS)
Sorry to startle you,

01:01:59.280 --> 01:02:01.560
but I wonder if I can have
just a moment of your time.

01:02:01.800 --> 01:02:04.600
Are you by any chance
friends with Littlefoot?

01:02:06.720 --> 01:02:07.960
We are!

01:02:09.280 --> 01:02:11.200
He says you should come with me.

01:02:11.640 --> 01:02:14.480
What's a Bigbeak doing underground?

01:02:14.840 --> 01:02:17.440
Well, that's an interesting story
and I'd love to tell all of you that.

01:02:17.520 --> 01:02:18.480
But first,

01:02:18.560 --> 01:02:20.480
maybe we should get you
away from that Sharptooth.

01:02:21.160 --> 01:02:22.640
(GROWLING)

01:02:24.800 --> 01:02:27.840
Honey, would you mind
giving that rock just a little shove?

01:02:29.240 --> 01:02:30.360
You got it!

01:02:33.920 --> 01:02:35.600
(STRAINING) Go!

01:02:38.040 --> 01:02:39.480
(ROARING)

01:02:39.520 --> 01:02:40.760
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:02:42.120 --> 01:02:43.080
Whoa!

01:02:44.120 --> 01:02:45.080
(STRAINING)

01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:47.360
(GROWLING)
(SCREAMING)

01:02:59.920 --> 01:03:01.360
(SIGHS)

01:03:02.520 --> 01:03:03.800
Littlefoot!

01:03:05.400 --> 01:03:06.840
Hi, everyone!

01:03:08.160 --> 01:03:10.200
Oh, Petrie miss you!

01:03:10.520 --> 01:03:12.280
Spike and me, too!

01:03:12.520 --> 01:03:14.160
(SOFT CHUCKLE)

01:03:15.040 --> 01:03:16.960
I'm so happy we're all together.

01:03:17.640 --> 01:03:19.960
I... I should have never left you.

01:03:24.480 --> 01:03:27.640
Yeah, well,
maybe we all shouldn't have left.

01:03:28.560 --> 01:03:30.280
I'm sorry, Littlefoot.

01:03:31.080 --> 01:03:32.320
Me, too.

01:03:35.800 --> 01:03:38.120
Etta, these are my friends.

01:03:38.200 --> 01:03:39.520
(LAUGHS)

01:03:39.680 --> 01:03:41.320
I can sure see that!

01:03:42.560 --> 01:03:44.960
Hey, look what me and Etta found.

01:03:47.840 --> 01:03:49.360
It's the moving water!

01:03:49.440 --> 01:03:51.280
It went under the ground.

01:03:51.320 --> 01:03:53.240
That's why we couldn't
find it before.

01:03:53.720 --> 01:03:56.600
I think this will take us
right to the Fire Mountain.

01:03:57.000 --> 01:03:59.600
I mean...
If you still want to go with me.

01:04:00.520 --> 01:04:02.360
I will go with you, Littlefoot.

01:04:02.840 --> 01:04:04.120
(MOANS IN AGREEMENT)

01:04:05.080 --> 01:04:06.520
Petrie, too.

01:04:07.120 --> 01:04:09.400
Hey, hey, hey!
Count me in.

01:04:12.320 --> 01:04:14.400
Well, what are we waiting for?

01:04:14.480 --> 01:04:16.000
Let's go!

01:04:16.880 --> 01:04:17.960
Jump!

01:04:18.040 --> 01:04:19.480
Whoo-hoo!

01:04:20.040 --> 01:04:21.080
(LAUGHS)

01:04:21.480 --> 01:04:23.200
The water's great!

01:04:23.960 --> 01:04:25.160
(SCREAMS)

01:04:25.720 --> 01:04:27.160
(YELLS)

01:04:28.960 --> 01:04:30.240
(LAUGHING)

01:04:30.320 --> 01:04:32.240
Look out below!

01:04:38.360 --> 01:04:39.840
ALL: Ooh! Ah!

01:04:42.400 --> 01:04:43.600
(SCREAMS)

01:04:44.520 --> 01:04:45.680
(LAUGHING)

01:04:49.240 --> 01:04:50.640
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

01:05:12.200 --> 01:05:14.120
(ALL GIGGLING)

01:05:21.880 --> 01:05:25.280
Look! Light!
We're coming out!

01:05:25.560 --> 01:05:27.560
Petrie see only sky.
(GASPS)

01:05:28.080 --> 01:05:30.160
CERA:
Oh, what does that mean?

01:05:31.000 --> 01:05:33.040
(GASPS) Falling water!

01:05:35.200 --> 01:05:36.440
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:05:43.440 --> 01:05:45.360
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:05:49.160 --> 01:05:50.520
Whoa!
(LAUGHING)

01:06:08.600 --> 01:06:10.480
(GIGGLING)
Ooh! That was the best!

01:06:10.800 --> 01:06:13.200
(GIGGLING)
I want to do that again!

01:06:13.240 --> 01:06:14.440
(MOANS IN AGREEMENT)

01:06:17.080 --> 01:06:18.720
Anybody know where we are?

01:06:19.160 --> 01:06:20.320
ETTA: Yep.

01:06:20.800 --> 01:06:23.120
I'm afraid I do.

01:06:26.760 --> 01:06:29.480
(ALL GASP)

01:06:31.640 --> 01:06:32.600
(EXHALES)

01:06:38.960 --> 01:06:40.840
Petrie like
the water more.

01:06:41.520 --> 01:06:42.760
What now?

01:06:44.280 --> 01:06:46.760
Etta, where did you say
you saw my dad?

01:07:00.600 --> 01:07:02.200
Just over that ridge,

01:07:03.160 --> 01:07:05.200
that's where your father fell.

01:07:06.360 --> 01:07:09.120
Littlefoot, you might not like
what you see.

01:07:13.880 --> 01:07:14.920
(GASPS)

01:07:17.640 --> 01:07:19.000
Littlefoot?

01:07:27.040 --> 01:07:28.160
(GASPS)

01:07:31.400 --> 01:07:32.400
Dad!

01:07:35.800 --> 01:07:36.720
Littlefoot?

01:07:40.520 --> 01:07:41.960
(ALL PANTING)

01:07:44.080 --> 01:07:46.080
(STUTTERING)
What are you doing here?

01:07:46.320 --> 01:07:48.000
We came to get you.

01:07:48.680 --> 01:07:50.920
Thank you, all of you.

01:07:51.160 --> 01:07:53.240
But my leg is stuck.

01:07:53.840 --> 01:07:55.920
There's nothing you can do.

01:07:59.160 --> 01:08:00.240
(SNIFFING)

01:08:01.080 --> 01:08:02.480
They came this way.

01:08:02.520 --> 01:08:03.640
(SNIFFING)

01:08:10.200 --> 01:08:11.680
(SNIFFING)

01:08:12.040 --> 01:08:13.040
Sharptooth!

01:08:13.640 --> 01:08:14.920
(SCREAMS)

01:08:16.920 --> 01:08:18.760
(YELLING) Sharptooth!
Nobody make a sound!

01:08:18.840 --> 01:08:20.720
Everybody needs to be very, very...

01:08:20.800 --> 01:08:22.359
(SOFTLY)
Quiet, Wild Arms.

01:08:22.439 --> 01:08:24.080
(ROARING)

01:08:28.319 --> 01:08:29.760
This way.
(SHUDDERING)

01:08:29.880 --> 01:08:31.319
(WHIMPERS)

01:08:43.880 --> 01:08:45.560
(WHIMPERING)
I wanna go home.

01:08:45.640 --> 01:08:46.800
(SHUSHING)

01:08:49.240 --> 01:08:52.160
Oh, no... Why...

01:08:57.720 --> 01:08:59.359
(ROARS)

01:09:03.520 --> 01:09:04.880
He's gone.
(SHIVERING)

01:09:07.160 --> 01:09:09.120
You hear that?
He's gone!

01:09:13.040 --> 01:09:16.040
(CLEARS THROAT)
He's gone.

01:09:16.120 --> 01:09:17.640
Isn't that great?

01:09:20.920 --> 01:09:23.040
There has to be
something we can do!

01:09:23.600 --> 01:09:25.200
(WHIMPERS)

01:09:25.279 --> 01:09:26.960
Me so sorry.

01:09:27.600 --> 01:09:30.160
Etta, please take them home.

01:09:30.479 --> 01:09:32.040
I am not going!

01:09:32.160 --> 01:09:33.399
(EXPLODES)

01:09:34.200 --> 01:09:35.479
(ALL GASPING)

01:09:38.439 --> 01:09:40.160
Littlefoot, your dad's right.

01:09:43.600 --> 01:09:45.920
You didn't give up on your herd.

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:47.920
I'm not giving up on you!

01:09:51.960 --> 01:09:53.600
We want to help, too.
ETTA: Uh-huh!

01:09:53.720 --> 01:09:54.920
(MOANS IN AGREEMENT)

01:10:04.680 --> 01:10:07.560
Cera, do you think you can
move that big rock?

01:10:08.600 --> 01:10:11.240
That one? It's huge!

01:10:11.880 --> 01:10:14.200
I know.
But you can do it.

01:10:16.440 --> 01:10:18.880
Look out, I'm coming through!

01:10:20.600 --> 01:10:23.480
Guys, Etta,
we're going to need a tree.

01:10:24.560 --> 01:10:25.880
Get that one.

01:10:25.960 --> 01:10:27.280
ETTA: Okay.
SPIKE: Mmm-hmm!

01:10:27.680 --> 01:10:29.160
What can Petrie do?

01:10:29.520 --> 01:10:30.840
Go up high.

01:10:30.920 --> 01:10:33.480
Let us know when
the flowing fire starts coming for us.

01:10:34.200 --> 01:10:35.440
Petrie will!

01:10:36.760 --> 01:10:37.840
Huh?

01:10:40.480 --> 01:10:41.840
Hang on!

01:10:43.520 --> 01:10:44.720
(GRUNTING)

01:10:48.040 --> 01:10:49.160
(GASPS)

01:10:49.680 --> 01:10:50.720
(GROWLING)

01:10:51.040 --> 01:10:52.120
(STRAINING)

01:10:57.560 --> 01:10:59.960
Cera, you can do it!

01:11:04.760 --> 01:11:06.160
Get ready!

01:11:06.280 --> 01:11:07.840
You're going down!

01:11:07.920 --> 01:11:09.680
(STRAINING)

01:11:10.720 --> 01:11:11.760
Yeah!

01:11:13.560 --> 01:11:14.520
Whoa!

01:11:21.720 --> 01:11:22.640
(GASPS)

01:11:28.400 --> 01:11:30.000
Yeah!

01:11:36.880 --> 01:11:38.200
Dad.

01:11:38.240 --> 01:11:39.680
Littlefoot.

01:11:41.160 --> 01:11:42.560
(BOTH STRAINING)

01:11:59.840 --> 01:12:02.440
Okay, put the end in here!

01:12:03.480 --> 01:12:04.680
(STRAINING)

01:12:07.760 --> 01:12:09.560
Everyone get ready!

01:12:09.680 --> 01:12:11.520
When I say, "Push down!"

01:12:12.440 --> 01:12:13.720
Hurry!

01:12:13.880 --> 01:12:16.720
Ready, set, push!

01:12:17.400 --> 01:12:18.840
(ALL STRAINING)

01:12:23.200 --> 01:12:24.320
(GRUNTING)

01:12:26.040 --> 01:12:27.160
(ALL STRAINING)

01:12:29.960 --> 01:12:31.000
Dad, now!

01:12:40.080 --> 01:12:41.560
Hey!

01:12:41.880 --> 01:12:43.800
Petrie think you should hurry!

01:12:46.720 --> 01:12:48.320
Go! Go! Go!

01:12:51.480 --> 01:12:52.800
(ALL GASPING)

01:12:58.160 --> 01:12:59.240
(BRON GRUNTS)

01:13:04.760 --> 01:13:06.120
(ALL CHEERING)

01:13:07.960 --> 01:13:09.120
MR. THREEHORN: Cera!

01:13:13.760 --> 01:13:14.720
Dad!

01:13:15.160 --> 01:13:16.560
(GIGGLING)

01:13:19.160 --> 01:13:20.960
Thank goodness.

01:13:25.600 --> 01:13:26.920
(MOANING HAPPILY)

01:13:30.360 --> 01:13:32.360
What are you doing way out here?

01:13:32.960 --> 01:13:34.360
We came to save you.

01:13:35.000 --> 01:13:37.920
Oh, we thank you but no need saving.

01:13:38.440 --> 01:13:40.480
This time we do saving.

01:13:41.160 --> 01:13:42.640
ETTA: Wild Arms!

01:13:43.040 --> 01:13:44.880
What are you doing back here?

01:13:45.720 --> 01:13:48.120
Well, Etta, I volunteered
to lead the rescue.

01:13:48.280 --> 01:13:49.720
That's what I'm doing here.

01:13:50.080 --> 01:13:51.080
(CHUCKLES)

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:54.000
You volunteered?

01:13:54.080 --> 01:13:55.120
Really?

01:13:56.760 --> 01:13:59.440
Well, uh...
(CHUCKLES) Yeah?

01:14:02.160 --> 01:14:03.600
(LAUGHING)

01:14:04.680 --> 01:14:06.040
Grandpa!

01:14:08.960 --> 01:14:11.360
I see you found your father.

01:14:11.480 --> 01:14:13.000
He did.

01:14:13.640 --> 01:14:15.000
We all did.

01:14:15.080 --> 01:14:16.720
(ALL AGREEING)

01:14:17.520 --> 01:14:19.680
You've got quite a group of friends.

01:14:20.720 --> 01:14:23.120
You remind me of someone I know.

01:14:27.520 --> 01:14:29.360
Come, everyone.

01:14:29.520 --> 01:14:31.800
Let's all go home.

01:14:33.800 --> 01:14:35.960
Finally someone who's sensible!

01:14:36.080 --> 01:14:37.320
Let's get out of here.

01:14:37.400 --> 01:14:38.840
(LAUGHING)

01:14:45.720 --> 01:14:47.920
NARRATOR:
<i>Littlefoot had found his father.</i>

01:14:49.040 --> 01:14:51.440
<i>And he found something else, too.</i>

01:14:52.120 --> 01:14:54.320
<i>Something he wasn't looking for.</i>

01:14:57.160 --> 01:15:01.280
<i>The realization that he and his friends</i>
<i>would always be together</i>

01:15:01.720 --> 01:15:03.600
<i>till the end of their days</i>

01:15:03.680 --> 01:15:05.680
<i>in the Land Before Time.</i>

